  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0b9f\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0b86\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b92\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b86\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b8f\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A modest improvement in garment export earnings compared to last year",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Compared to last year, this year's garment export income has increased to 446 dollars in May. This is a 30 percent increase. The Forum of Joint Garments Unions has appreciated this development.",
        "The Forum of Joint Garment Societies also appreciated that the country's garment industry has faced unprecedented challenges and continued to contribute towards achieving its goals.",
        "The garment industry forms the backbone of the national economy, contributing about 6 percent of Sri Lanka's GDP and nearly half of all exports. As the industry continues to face significant disruptions due to disruptions in energy supply and manufacturing operations, the sector's export earnings are expected to rise by 16 to 22 percent by May.",
        "Commenting on this, Yohan Lorenz, General Secretary of the Confederation of Apparel Associations, said, 'We hope to reach the industry target of 6 billion US dollars by the end of 2022. However we are well aware that there are significant challenges to overcome first. It is therefore important to provide all possible support for the continuity of operations in the industry.",
        "\"Apart from ensuring that large garment manufacturers sustain their production, it is necessary to prioritize support for small and medium-sized garment manufacturers, a key segment of the industry who face severe challenges in day-to-day operations,\" he said.",
        "Despite the unprecedented uncertainty the country is currently facing, unstable global market conditions and rising costs of raw materials and production, Sri Lanka's apparel industry has contributed significantly to the national economy.",
        "Despite the current crisis, high trends in export performance recorded a year-on-year growth of 17 per cent up to June and the continued inflow of foreign direct investment (FDI) in Sri Lanka still reflects a positive attitude towards apparel within the country. It is worth noting that investments worth USD 73 million have been made so far for the expansion of the apparel sector by 2022, out of USD 94 million in apparel investment."
      ],
